idx.description: A unique study index or sample identifier for tracking.

Proteomics_Participant_ID.description: Unique identifier for a participant within the proteomics study.

Case_excluded.description: Indicates whether the participant's case was excluded from the primary study analysis.

Proteomics_TMT_batch.description: The sequential batch number for Tandem Mass Tag (TMT) proteomics experiments.

Proteomics_TMT_plex.description: The specific plex number within a TMT batch, identifying a multiplexed sample set.

Proteomics_TMT_channel.description: TMT (Tandem Mass Tag) channel identifier used for multiplexed quantitative proteomics experiments.

Proteomics_Parent_Sample_IDs.description: Identifier for the parent sample from which the proteomics aliquot was derived.

Proteomics_Aliquot_ID.description: Unique identifier for the specific proteomics aliquot used in the experiment.

Proteomics_Tumor_Normal.description: Classification of the sample tissue status, indicating if it is tumor, adjacent normal, or another normal tissue type.

Proteomics_OCT.description: Indicates whether the sample was embedded in Optimal Cutting Temperature (OCT) compound for preservation.

Country.description: The country where the patient is located or from.

Histologic_Grade_FIGO.description: The FIGO (International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics) histologic grade of the tumor, indicating differentiation.

Myometrial_invasion_Specify.description: The extent of myometrial invasion by the tumor.

Histologic_type.description: The histologic type of the tumor, classifying its cellular origin and morphology.

Treatment_naive.description: Indicates whether the patient is naive to treatment (i.e., has not received prior treatment).

Tumor_purity.description: The purity of the tumor sample, indicating the proportion of tumor cells in a sample.

Path_Stage_Primary_Tumor-pT.description: Pathological T-stage for primary tumor, describing the size and extent of the primary tumor.

Path_Stage_Reg_Lymph_Nodes-pN.description: Pathological N-stage for regional lymph nodes, describing the involvement of nearby lymph nodes.

Clin_Stage_Dist_Mets-cM.description: Clinical M-stage for distant metastasis, indicating the presence or absence of distant spread of the tumor based on clinical assessment.

Path_Stage_Dist_Mets-pM.description: Pathological M-stage for distant metastasis, indicating the presence or absence of distant spread of the tumor based on pathological examination.
enum: No pathologic evidence of distant metastasis

tumor_Stage-Pathological.description: Pathological tumor stage, based on surgical and pathological examination.

FIGO_stage.description: International Federation of Gynecology and Obstetrics (FIGO) staging for gynecological cancers.

LVSI.description: Lymphovascular Space Invasion, indicating the presence (1) or absence (0) of tumor cells in lymphatic or blood vessels.

BMI.description: Body Mass Index, calculated as weight in kilograms divided by the square of height in meters.

Age.description: Age of the patient in years.

Diabetes.description: Indicates whether the patient has a history of diabetes.

enum: Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander

Ethnicity.description: The patient's ethnic identification, primarily Hispanic or Latino origin.

Gender.description: The patient's biological or reported gender.

Tumor_Site.description: The anatomical site where the primary tumor is located.

Tumor_Site_Other.description: Describes additional or specific sites of tumor involvement, often a detailed anatomical location.

Tumor_Focality.description: Indicates whether the tumor presents as a single lesion (unifocal) or multiple distinct lesions (multifocal).

Tumor_Size_cm.description: The maximum dimension of the tumor measured in centimeters.

Estrogen_Receptor.description: Status of estrogen receptor expression, typically determined by immunohistochemistry (IHC).

Estrogen_Receptor_%.description: Percentage of tumor cells expressing estrogen receptor, typically by immunohistochemistry (IHC).

Progesterone_Receptor.description: Status of Progesterone Receptor (PR) expression, typically determined by immunohistochemistry (IHC).

Progesterone_Receptor_%.description: Percentage of tumor cells expressing Progesterone Receptor (PR), determined by immunohistochemistry (IHC).

MLH1.description: Status of MLH1 protein expression, typically determined by immunohistochemistry (IHC) for Mismatch Repair (MMR) deficiency.

MLH2.description: Status of MLH2 (often refers to MSH2 in MMR) protein expression, typically determined by immunohistochemistry (IHC) for Mismatch Repair (MMR) deficiency.

MSH6.description: Status of MSH6 protein expression, typically determined by immunohistochemistry (IHC) for Mismatch Repair (MMR) deficiency.

PMS2.description: Immunohistochemistry (IHC) result for PMS2 protein expression, indicating its nuclear staining pattern. PMS2 is a DNA mismatch repair protein.

p53.description: Immunohistochemistry (IHC) result for p53 protein expression, often indicating its cellular localization and intensity. p53 is a tumor suppressor protein.

Other_IHC_specify.description: Free text field to specify other immunohistochemistry (IHC) findings, stains, or interpretations not covered by predefined markers.

MLH1_Promoter_Hypermethylation.description: Result indicating the promoter hypermethylation status of the MLH1 gene. Hypermethylation can lead to gene silencing and is relevant in certain cancer types.

Num_full_term_pregnancies.description: The reported number of full-term pregnancies experienced by the patient.

EPIC_Bcells.description: Estimated proportion of B cells in the immune microenvironment, derived using the EPIC computational deconvolution method from bulk transcriptomic data.

EPIC_CAFs.description: Estimated proportion of Cancer-Associated Fibroblasts (CAFs) in the immune microenvironment, derived using the EPIC computational deconvolution method from bulk transcriptomic data.

EPIC_CD4_Tcells.description: Estimated proportion of CD4+ T cells in the immune microenvironment, derived using the EPIC computational deconvolution method from bulk transcriptomic data.

EPIC_CD8_Tcells.description: Estimated proportion of CD8+ T cells in the immune microenvironment, derived using the EPIC computational deconvolution method from bulk transcriptomic data.

EPIC_Endothelial.description: Estimated proportion of Endothelial cells in the immune microenvironment, derived using the EPIC computational deconvolution method from bulk transcriptomic data.

EPIC_Macrophages.description: Proportion of Macrophages estimated by the EPIC deconvolution method, indicating the abundance of these immune cells.

EPIC_NKcells.description: Proportion of Natural Killer (NK) cells estimated by the EPIC deconvolution method, reflecting their abundance in the sample.

EPIC_otherCells.description: Proportion of other cell types (non-specific, beyond Macrophages and NK cells) estimated by the EPIC deconvolution method.

CIBERSORT_B _cells _naive.description: Proportion of naive B cells estimated by the CIBERSORT deconvolution method, representing immature B lymphocytes.

CIBERSORT_B _cells _memory.description: Proportion of memory B cells estimated by the CIBERSORT deconvolution method, indicating B lymphocytes that have encountered antigens.

CIBERSORT_Plasma _cells.description: Estimated fraction of Plasma B cells as determined by CIBERSORT analysis.

CIBERSORT_T _cells _CD8.description: Estimated fraction of CD8+ T cells as determined by CIBERSORT analysis.

CIBERSORT_T _cells _CD4 _naive.description: Estimated fraction of naive CD4+ T cells as determined by CIBERSORT analysis.

CIBERSORT_T _cells _CD4 _memory _resting.description: Estimated fraction of resting memory CD4+ T cells as determined by CIBERSORT analysis.

CIBERSORT_T _cells _CD4 _memory _activat.description: Estimated fraction of activated memory CD4+ T cells as determined by CIBERSORT analysis.

CIBERSORT_T _cells _follicular _helper.description: CIBERSORT-derived estimated fraction or score of follicular helper T cells in an immune cell profile.

CIBERSORT_T _cells _regulatory _(Tregs).description: CIBERSORT-derived estimated fraction or score of regulatory T cells (Tregs) in an immune cell profile.

CIBERSORT_T _cells _gamma _delta.description: CIBERSORT-derived estimated fraction or score of gamma-delta T cells in an immune cell profile.

CIBERSORT_NK _cells _resting.description: CIBERSORT-derived estimated fraction or score of resting natural killer (NK) cells in an immune cell profile.

CIBERSORT_NK _cells _activated.description: CIBERSORT-derived estimated fraction or score of activated natural killer (NK) cells in an immune cell profile.

CIBERSORT_Monocytes.description: CIBERSORT-derived estimated fraction of Monocytes in a sample.

CIBERSORT_Macrophages _M0.description: CIBERSORT-derived estimated fraction of M0 (unpolarized) Macrophages in a sample.

CIBERSORT_Macrophages _M1.description: CIBERSORT-derived estimated fraction of M1 (pro-inflammatory) Macrophages in a sample.

CIBERSORT_Macrophages _M2.description: CIBERSORT-derived estimated fraction of M2 (anti-inflammatory) Macrophages in a sample.

CIBERSORT_Dendritic _cells _resting.description: CIBERSORT-derived estimated fraction of resting Dendritic cells in a sample.

CIBERSORT_Dendritic _cells _activated.description: Fraction or proportion of activated dendritic cells estimated by CIBERSORT.

CIBERSORT_Mast _cells _resting.description: Fraction or proportion of resting mast cells estimated by CIBERSORT.

CIBERSORT_Mast _cells _activated.description: Fraction or proportion of activated mast cells estimated by CIBERSORT.

CIBERSORT_Eosinophils.description: Fraction or proportion of eosinophils estimated by CIBERSORT.

CIBERSORT_Neutrophils.description: Fraction or proportion of neutrophils estimated by CIBERSORT.

CIBERSORT_Absolute _score.description: CIBERSORT absolute score, indicating the estimated abundance of various immune cell types in a sample. Ranges typically from 0 to 1.

ESTIMATE_StromalScore.description: ESTIMATE stromal score, reflecting the presence and proportion of stromal cells in the tumor microenvironment.

ESTIMATE_ImmuneScore.description: ESTIMATE immune score, reflecting the presence and proportion of immune cells infiltrating the tumor microenvironment.

ESTIMATE_ESTIMATEScore.description: ESTIMATE score, representing the combined stromal and immune cell infiltration, which can be inversely correlated with tumor purity.

Stemness_score.description: A score quantifying the stem-like properties of cancer cells within a tumor sample. Typically ranges from 0 to 1, where higher values indicate increased stemness.

ER_ESR1.description: Expression level or activity score of Estrogen Receptor 1 (ESR1) gene.

PR_PGR.description: Expression level or activity score of Progesterone Receptor (PGR) gene.

Pathway_activity_EGFR.description: Activity score of the Epidermal Growth Factor Receptor (EGFR) signaling pathway.

Pathway_activity_Hypoxia.description: Activity score related to the Hypoxia pathway.

Pathway_activity_JAK.STAT.description: Activity score of the JAK-STAT signaling pathway.

Pathway_activity_MAPK.description: Quantified activity score for the Mitogen-Activated Protein Kinase (MAPK) signaling pathway, derived from gene expression data.

Pathway_activity_NFkB.description: Quantified activity score for the Nuclear Factor kappa-light-chain-enhancer of activated B cells (NF-κB) signaling pathway, derived from gene expression data.

Pathway_activity_PI3K.description: Quantified activity score for the Phosphoinositide 3-kinase (PI3K) signaling pathway, derived from gene expression data.

Pathway_activity_TGFb.description: Quantified activity score for the Transforming Growth Factor-beta (TGF-β) signaling pathway, derived from gene expression data.

Pathway_activity_TNFa.description: Quantified activity score for the Tumor Necrosis Factor-alpha (TNF-α) signaling pathway, derived from gene expression data.

Pathway_activity_Trail.description: Pathway activity level for TRAIL (TNF-Related Apoptosis-Inducing Ligand) signaling pathway, derived from gene expression data.

Pathway_activity_VEGF.description: Pathway activity level for VEGF (Vascular Endothelial Growth Factor) signaling pathway, derived from gene expression data.

Pathway_activity_p53.description: Pathway activity level for p53 signaling pathway, derived from gene expression data.

TP53_ATM.description: Presence (1) or absence (0) of a genomic variation or mutation affecting both TP53 and ATM genes.

TP53_CHEK2.description: Presence (1) or absence (0) of a genomic variation or mutation affecting both TP53 and CHEK2 genes.

TP53_MDM4.description: Genomic variation status (e.g., mutation, amplification, or deletion) associated with the interaction or pathway involving TP53 and MDM4.

TP53_RPS6KA3.description: Genomic variation status (e.g., mutation, amplification, or deletion) associated with the interaction or pathway involving TP53 and RPS6KA3.

TP53_TP53.description: Genomic variation status (e.g., mutation, amplification, or deletion) within the TP53 gene itself.

TP53_pathway.description: Overall genomic alteration status of the TP53 signaling pathway, indicating whether the pathway is affected by any variations.

PI3K_AKT1.description: Genomic variation status (e.g., mutation, amplification, or deletion) associated with the PI3K-AKT1 signaling axis.

PI3K_AKT2.description: Genomic variation status, alteration, or activity level of the AKT2 gene, associated with the PI3K pathway.

PI3K_AKT3.description: Genomic variation status, alteration, or activity level of the AKT3 gene, associated with the PI3K pathway.

PI3K_DEPDC5.description: Genomic variation status, alteration, or activity level of the DEPDC5 gene, associated with the PI3K pathway.

PI3K_DEPTOR.description: Genomic variation status, alteration, or activity level of the DEPTOR gene, associated with the PI3K pathway.

PI3K_INPP4B.description: Genomic variation status, alteration, or activity level of the INPP4B gene, associated with the PI3K pathway.

PI3K_MAPKAP1.description: Genomic variant status or indicator for the PI3K pathway gene MAPKAP1 (Mitogen-Activated Protein Kinase Associated Protein 1), often representing presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of a mutation or alteration.

PI3K_MLST8.description: Genomic variant status or indicator for the PI3K pathway gene MLST8 (mTOR Associated Protein, LST8 Homolog), often representing presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of a mutation or alteration.

PI3K_MTOR.description: Genomic variant status or indicator for the central PI3K pathway gene MTOR (Mechanistic Target Of Rapamycin), often representing presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of a mutation or alteration.

PI3K_NPRL2.description: Genomic variant status or indicator for the PI3K pathway gene NPRL2 (NPR3-Like Protein 2), often representing presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of a mutation or alteration.

PI3K_NPRL3.description: Genomic variant status or indicator for the PI3K pathway gene NPRL3 (NPR3-Like Protein 3), often representing presence (1.0) or absence (0.0) of a mutation or alteration.

PI3K_PDK1.description: Genomic variant status or mutation presence for the PI3K pathway gene PDK1 (3-phosphoinositide-dependent protein kinase 1). A value of 1 typically indicates a variant or positive status, while 0 indicates wild-type or negative status.

PI3K_PIK3CA.description: Genomic variant status or mutation presence for the PI3K pathway gene PIK3CA (Phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphate 3-kinase catalytic subunit alpha). A value of 1 typically indicates a variant or positive status, while 0 indicates wild-type or negative status.

PI3K_PIK3CB.description: Genomic variant status or mutation presence for the PI3K pathway gene PIK3CB (Phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphate 3-kinase catalytic subunit beta). A value of 1 typically indicates a variant or positive status, while 0 indicates wild-type or negative status.

PI3K_PIK3R1.description: Genomic variant status or mutation presence for the PI3K pathway gene PIK3R1 (Phosphoinositide-3-kinase regulatory subunit 1). A value of 1 typically indicates a variant or positive status, while 0 indicates wild-type or negative status.

PI3K_PIK3R2.description: Genomic variant status or mutation presence for the PI3K pathway gene PIK3R2 (Phosphoinositide-3-kinase regulatory subunit 2). A value of 1 typically indicates a variant or positive status, while 0 indicates wild-type or negative status.

PI3K_PPP2R1A.description: Presence of a genomic variant (mutation or alteration) in the PPP2R1A gene within the PI3K signaling pathway. A value of 1.0 indicates the presence of a variant, and 0.0 indicates no variant detected (wild-type).

PI3K_PTEN.description: Presence of a genomic variant (mutation or alteration) in the PTEN gene within the PI3K signaling pathway. A value of 1.0 indicates the presence of a variant, and 0.0 indicates no variant detected (wild-type).

PI3K_RHEB.description: Presence of a genomic variant (mutation or alteration) in the RHEB gene within the PI3K signaling pathway. A value of 1.0 indicates the presence of a variant, and 0.0 indicates no variant detected (wild-type).

PI3K_RICTOR.description: Presence of a genomic variant (mutation or alteration) in the RICTOR gene within the PI3K signaling pathway. A value of 1.0 indicates the presence of a variant, and 0.0 indicates no variant detected (wild-type).

PI3K_RPS6.description: Presence of a genomic variant (mutation or alteration) in the RPS6 gene within the PI3K signaling pathway. A value of 1.0 indicates the presence of a variant, and 0.0 indicates no variant detected (wild-type).

PI3K_RPS6KB1.description: Presence or absence of a genomic variant in the RPS6KB1 gene within the PI3K signaling pathway.

PI3K_RPTOR.description: Presence or absence of a genomic variant in the RPTOR gene within the PI3K signaling pathway.

PI3K_STK11.description: Presence or absence of a genomic variant in the STK11 gene within the PI3K signaling pathway.

PI3K_TSC1.description: Presence or absence of a genomic variant in the TSC1 gene within the PI3K signaling pathway.

PI3K_TSC2.description: Presence or absence of a genomic variant in the TSC2 gene within the PI3K signaling pathway.

PI3K_pathway.description: Indicates the status of the PI3K signaling pathway, often represented as 1 for altered/activated and 0 for unaltered/inactivated.

HRD_BRCA1.description: Indicates Homologous Recombination Deficiency (HRD) status specifically associated with BRCA1 mutations or alterations (1 for present, 0 for absent).

HRD_BRCA2.description: Indicates Homologous Recombination Deficiency (HRD) status specifically associated with BRCA2 mutations or alterations (1 for present, 0 for absent).

HRD_BRCA1_or_BRCA2.description: Indicates Homologous Recombination Deficiency (HRD) status associated with either BRCA1 or BRCA2 mutations or alterations (1 for present, 0 for absent).

CNV_DEL.description: A quantitative score or measure representing the extent or frequency of copy number variation deletions.

CNV_AMP.description: Copy Number Variation (CNV) amplification score or magnitude, representing the degree of genomic amplification.

CNV_class.description: Classification or categorization of Copy Number Variation (CNV) events, typically indicating severity or type of alteration.

CNV_idx.description: Index or score representing a Copy Number Variation (CNV) event, possibly related to its size, frequency, or impact.

CNV_1q_DEL.description: Copy Number Variation (CNV) deletion score or magnitude specifically for chromosome arm 1q.

CNV_3q_DEL.description: Copy Number Variation (CNV) deletion score or magnitude specifically for chromosome arm 3q.

CNV_4q_DEL.description: Copy number variation indicating a deletion event on the long arm (q arm) of chromosome 4. Represents the magnitude of the deletion.

CNV_1q_AMP.description: Copy number variation indicating an amplification event on the long arm (q arm) of chromosome 1. Represents the magnitude of the amplification.

CNV_3q_AMP.description: Copy number variation indicating an amplification event on the long arm (q arm) of chromosome 3. Represents the magnitude of the amplification.

CNV_4q_AMP.description: Copy number variation indicating an amplification event on the long arm (q arm) of chromosome 4. Represents the magnitude of the amplification.

Purity_Immune.description: The estimated proportion of immune cells within a tumor sample, often used to assess tumor microenvironment composition or purity.

Purity_Cancer.description: The estimated proportion of cancer cells in a tumor sample, indicating tumor cellularity.

Purity_Stroma.description: The estimated proportion of stromal cells (connective tissue) in a tumor sample.

MSI_status.description: Microsatellite instability (MSI) status, indicating the presence of genetic hypermutability.

POLE_subtype.description: Polymerase Epsilon (POLE) mutation status, often associated with specific tumor subtypes.

JAK1_MS_INDEL.description: Status of microsatellite indels (insertions/deletions) in the JAK1 gene.

JAK1_Mutation.description: Mutation status or type observed in the Janus Kinase 1 (JAK1) gene.

Log2_variant_per_Mbp.description: Log2-transformed count of all genomic variants per megabase pair.

Log2_SNP_per_Mbp.description: Log2-transformed count of Single Nucleotide Polymorphism (SNP) variants per megabase pair.

Log2_INDEL_per_Mbp.description: Log2-transformed count of Insertion/Deletion (INDEL) variants per megabase pair.

Log2_variant_total.description: Log2-transformed total count of all genomic variants.

Log2_SNP_total.description: Log2 transformed total count or frequency of Single Nucleotide Polymorphisms (SNPs).

Log2_INDEL_total.description: Log2 transformed total count or frequency of Insertions and Deletions (INDELs).

Genomics_subtype.description: Genomic subtype classification of a sample, indicating specific genomic alterations or profiles.

Mutation_signature_C>A.description: Frequency or score of the C>A (Cytosine to Adenine) mutation signature, indicating specific mutational processes.

Mutation_signature_C>G.description: Frequency or score of the C>G (Cytosine to Guanine) mutation signature, indicating specific mutational processes.

Mutation_signature_C>T.description: The percentage or frequency contribution of C>T mutations to a specific mutation signature.

Mutation_signature_T>C.description: The percentage or frequency contribution of T>C mutations to a specific mutation signature.

Mutation_signature_T>A.description: The percentage or frequency contribution of T>A mutations to a specific mutation signature.

Mutation_signature_T>G.description: The percentage or frequency contribution of T>G mutations to a specific mutation signature.

WXS_normal_sample_type.description: The type of normal sample collected for Whole Exome Sequencing (WXS) analysis.

WXS_normal_filename.description: Filename of the Whole Exome Sequencing (WXS) normal sample data.

WXS_normal_UUID.description: Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) for the Whole Exome Sequencing (WXS) normal sample data file.

WXS_tumor_sample_type.description: Type of the Whole Exome Sequencing (WXS) tumor sample.

WXS_tumor_filename.description: Filename of the Whole Exome Sequencing (WXS) tumor sample data.

WXS_tumor_UUID.description: Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) for the Whole Exome Sequencing (WXS) tumor sample data file.

WGS_normal_sample_type.description: Type of sample used for Whole Genome Sequencing (WGS) from normal tissue.

WGS_normal_UUID.description: Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) for the normal sample used in Whole Genome Sequencing (WGS).

WGS_tumor_sample_type.description: Type of sample used for Whole Genome Sequencing (WGS) from tumor tissue.

WGS_tumor_UUID.description: Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) for the tumor sample used in Whole Genome Sequencing (WGS).

RNAseq_R1_sample_type.description: Type of sample used for the first replicate (R1) of RNA sequencing (RNA-seq).

RNAseq_R1_filename.description: Filename for the first read (R1) of RNA sequencing data.

RNAseq_R1_UUID.description: Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) for the first read (R1) RNA sequencing data file.

RNAseq_R2_sample_type.description: Type of sample from which the RNA sequencing data (R2) was derived.

RNAseq_R2_filename.description: Filename for the second read (R2) of RNA sequencing data.

RNAseq_R2_UUID.description: Universally Unique Identifier (UUID) for the second read (R2) RNA sequencing data file.

miRNAseq_sample_type.description: Type of sample from which miRNA sequencing data was obtained (e.g., Tumor, Adjacent Normal tissue).

miRNAseq_UUID.description: Unique identifier (UUID) for the miRNA sequencing sample or data file.

Methylation_available.description: Indicates whether methylation data is available for the corresponding sample.

Methylation_quality.description: Quality assessment status of the methylation data.
